Node.Notes: Uncertain. Tree assumes something like wisdom [is] supreme. Alternatively, the beginning of wisdom [is this].
The lifepath of righteous people is like the light of dawn whose brightness increases until it is broad daylight (safe and unthreatened by unseen dangers in contrast to v. 19).
The heart is pictured as a water source from which life flows, indicating that a person's life is determined by thoughts/desires etc. stored in the heart.

Meaning of verse uncertain. If related to next verse, maybe something like "Look straight ahead to where you are going. Don't look around. Know where you are headed." If figurative for an honest approach, something like "let your eyes be fixed well on anyone in front of you; look straight ahead of you with openness."
